50|$|The Afghan Embassy in Ottawa in an {{interview}} with CTVS News condemned the murders of four members of a Montreal family originally from Afghanistan. The embassy called the deaths of the three teenaged sisters and their father's first wife <b>a</b> heinous <b>crime</b> <b>against</b> <b>humanity.</b> Moreover, they claimed that this kind of crime is not part of Afghan or Islamic culture and is not acceptable in any way.|$|R
